  <title>Cogl.IndicesType</title>
  <p>You should aim to use the smallest data type that gives you enough
range, since it reduces the size of your index array and can help
reduce the demand on memory bandwidth.</p>  <p>Note that <link xref="Cogl.IndicesType"/>.int is only supported if the
<link xref="Cogl.FeatureID"/>.ogl_feature_id_unsigned_int_indices feature is available. This
should always be available on OpenGL but on OpenGL ES it will only
be available if the GL_OES_element_index_uint extension is
advertized.</p>

